                <head>31. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>At the 285th meeting of the National Security Council on May 17, the President,
                    Secretary <persName corresp="#p_WCE1">Wilson</persName>, Governor <persName
                        corresp="#p_SHE1">Stassen</persName>, and <persName corresp="#p_RAAW1"
                        >Admiral Radford</persName> discussed the outmoded character of current
                        <gloss target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> planning and current <gloss
                        target="#t_NATO1">NATO</gloss> force levels in terms of nuclear warfare. The
                    memorandum of discussion at the meeting is is scheduled for publication in the
                    compilation on national security policy in a forthcoming volume of <hi
                        rend="italic">Foreign Relations</hi>.</p>
            </div>
